1. A detailed review has been prepared on the adoption of national minimum energy performance standards in Kazakhstan, containing an analysis of the current regulatory framework, benchmarking and comparative analysis of the level of energy efficiency with other countries; 
2. A contact working group, comprising representatives of key ministries and departments, development institutions and expert organizations, was set up for public discussion and agreeing with all stakeholders the adoption and implementation of energy efficiency standards, as well as other technical issues (labeling, normative documents, regulations) related to the project activities; 
3. Energy consumption analysis by motors, electric drives and distribution transformers has been carried out by sectors, large industrial enterprises and regions of the Republic of Kazakhstan; 
4. Recommendations for improving the methodology for conducting energy audit in the part of the audit of electric motors and transformers at industrial enterprises have been developed
5. An analysis of the current situation and existing sectoral issues has been prepared, and recommendations have been developed for developing a system for monitoring and control over compliance with standards and technical parameters of energy efficiency by household appliances and equipment. Detailed list of local laboratories for further interaction has been compiled, and a range of interested organizations for cooperation and assessing the potential of the existing national testing base has been identified;
